# Identity federation

Let **external identities assume roles** — no IAM user, no long-lived password.

## Two protocols

- **SAML 2.0** — enterprise IdPs (ADFS, Okta, Ping) → `AssumeRoleWithSAML`
- **OIDC** — Cognito, Google, EKS, GitHub Actions → `AssumeRoleWithWebIdentity`

Prove yourself to the IdP → AWS vends a **short-lived role session**.

## IAM Identity Center — the modern way

- Lives in the **management account**; one source of truth (its directory, AD, or Okta / Entra ID)
- **One sign-on portal** → every account + role; calls `AssumeRole` behind the scenes

## Permission set — its unit

Template of policies (+ optional boundary, session length). Define once → provisions a hidden role per account; update once → updates everywhere.

**Default to Identity Center over per-account IAM users.**
